Sentencas: The performance of PrBaCo2O5+delta Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 (PrBC + SDC) composites as electrodes of intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells is investigated.
Titulo: Assessment of PrBaCo2O5+δ + Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 composites prepared by physical mixing as electrodes of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The effects of SDC content on the performance and properties of the electrodes, including thermal expansion, DC conductivity, oxygen desorption, area specific resistance (ASR) and cathodic overpotential are evaluated.
Titulo: Assessment of PrBaCo2O5+δ + Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 composites prepared by physical mixing as electrodes of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The thermal expansion coefficient and electrical conductivity of the electrode decreases with an increase in SDC content.
Titulo: Assessment of PrBaCo2O5+δ + Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 composites prepared by physical mixing as electrodes of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: However, the electrical conductivity of a composite electrode containing 50 wt% SDC reaches 150S cm(-1) at 600 degrees C. Among the various electrodes under investigation, an electrode containing 30 wt% SDC exhibits superior electrochemical performance.
Titulo: Assessment of PrBaCo2O5+δ + Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 composites prepared by physical mixing as electrodes of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: A peak power density of approximately 1150 and 573 mW cm(-2) is reached at 650 and 550 degrees C, respectively, for an anode-supported thin-film SDC electrolyte cell with the optimal composite electrode.
Titulo: Assessment of PrBaCo2O5+δ + Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 composites prepared by physical mixing as electrodes of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The improved performance of a composite electrode containing 70 wt% PrBC and 30 wt% SDC is attributed to a reduction in the diffusion path of oxygen-ions within the electrode, which is a result of a three-dimensional oxygen-ion diffusion path in SDC and a one-dimensional diffusion path in PrBC.
Titulo: Assessment of PrBaCo2O5+δ + Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 composites prepared by physical mixing as electrodes of solid oxide fuel cells
